Hamilton Census Tracts with select demographic information from the 2011 Census of Canada.

Source: R/isdas-package.R
Hamilton_CT.Rd

A simple feature (sf) dataframe of Hamilton Census Metropolitan Area (CMA) Census Tracts (CTs) with demographic information from the 2011 Census. The projection is: EPSG: 26917 proj4string: "+proj=utm +zone=17 +ellps=GRS80 +towgs84=0,0,0,0,0,0,0 +units=m +no_defs"

Usage

data(Hamilton_CT)

Format

A SpatialPolygonsDataDrame with 188 rows and 20 variables

Source

https://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2011/geo/bound-limit/bound-limit-2011-eng.cfm

Details

  • ID. Unique Identifier of Area

  • AREA. Area of CT in sq.km.

  • TRACT. Unique Identifier of Census Tract

  • POPULATION. 2011 Population count in Census Tract

  • POP_DENSITY. Population density in Census Tract

  • AGE_LESS_20. Population aged less than 20 years old

  • AGE_20_TO_24. Population aged 20 to 24 years old

  • AGE_25_TO_29. Population aged 25 to 29 years old

  • AGE_30_TO_34. Population aged 30 to 34 years old

  • AGE_34_TO_39. Population aged 35 to 39 years old

  • AGE_40_TO_44. Population aged 40 to 44 years old

  • AGE_45_TO_49. Population aged 45 to 49 years old

  • AGE_50_TO_54. Population aged 50 to 54 years old

  • AGE_55_TO_59. Population aged 54 to 59 years old

  • AGE_60_TO_64. Population aged 60 to 64 years old

  • AGE_65_TO_69. Population aged 65 to 69 years old

  • AGE_70_TO_74. Population aged 70 to 74 years old

  • AGE_75_TO_79. Population aged 75 to 79 years old

  • AGE_80_TO_84. Population aged 80 to 84 years old

  • AGE_MORE_85. Population aged 85 years and older
